cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper analyzes a large-scale snapshot of del.icio.us, a social bookmarking website, and investigates the growth of the vocabulary size in the system. This falls under the scope of information retrieval, as it involves analyzing and organizing information for efficient retrieval. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper studies the collaborative tagging system of del.icio.us, which involves social interactions between users and the sharing of information. This falls under the scope of social and information networks, as it involves the analysis of network structures and dynamics. 
3. cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) - The paper may also fall under the scope of software development and programming, as it involves the analysis of a software system (del.icio.us) and the growth of its vocabulary size over time. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper may also fall under the scope of computation and language, as it involves the analysis of the growth of vocabulary size in written text (tags) and the investigation of non-trivial cognitive processes in collaborative tagging. 
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper may also fall under the scope of computers and society, as it involves the analysis of a social bookmarking website and the social interactions between users in collaborative tagging.
